name: Search Disorder
description:
Search disorder.
The more I try to know who I am, the more I get lost in the ways of the mind, creating an even greater emptiness than I had, realizing, with each step, that I am nobody. Picking up my house I am stirring the dirt that accumulates in the corners, twisting my being, fighting with my demons, suffering the greatest anguish of my life, visiting all the rooms of my house, until I find the illuminated one.
